Key Match Events: In the 4th ODI of the series between England and Australia, England set a challenging target of 312 runs, losing just 5 wickets in 39 overs.
Harry Brook led the charge with an impressive 87 runs off 58 balls.
Ben Duckett provided solid support with 63 runs from 62 balls.
Liam Livingstone made a rapid contribution, scoring 62 runs in just 27 deliveries.
Australia struggled against England’s formidable bowling attack, being bowled out for a mere 126 runs in 24.4 overs.
Travis Head was the top scorer for Australia with 34 runs off 23 balls.
Captain Mitchell Marsh added 28 runs from 34 balls.
Alex Carey managed only 13 runs off 22 balls.
England’s bowlers executed their plans effectively, taking quick wickets and limiting runs.
England secured a convincing 186-run victory in the 4th ODI.
Pre-Game Insights: The 5th ODI of the Australia Tour of England 2024 will see the clash between England and Australia at the County Ground, Bristol on Sunday, 29 September 2024.
The series is leveled up with a 2-2 margin, making the 5th ODI the decider match.
The pitch at County Ground, Bristol is known for its speed and bounce, favoring pace bowlers.
The weather in Bristol is favorable for the match with minimal chance of rain and clear skies.
Historical data indicates that teams batting first typically hold an advantage at this venue.
